    <body>
        <div xml:id="NA388-kiḷavi">
            <p type="edition">1. itu varaivu nīṭa āṟṟāḷākiya tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ (EN, ER, ET: talaimakaṉ; EV: talaivi talaivaṉ) ciṟaippuṟamākac (ET: talaivi) colliyatu.
                2. “maṉaiyuḷ vēṟupaṭātu āṟṟiṉāy” eṉṟāṭkut talaimakaḷ colliyatūumām.</p>
            <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what SHE said when [HE] was behind the fence to the confidante who had become unable to bear it when the marriage was delayed. 2. It is also what SHE said to the one who said “in the house you have been able to bear it without undergoing changes”.</p>
            </div>
      <div xml:id="NA388">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            amma vāḻi tōḻi naṉṉutaṟ</l>
<l>            kiyāṅkā yiṉṟukol pacappē nōṉpurik</l>
<l>            kayiṟukaṭai yātta kaṭunaṭai yeṟiyuḷit</l>
<l>            tiṇṭimiṟ paratava roṇcuṭark koḷīi</l>
<l>            naṭunāḷ vēṭṭam pōki vaikaṟaik</l>
<l>            kaṭaṉmīṉ ṟantu kāṉaṟ kuvaii</l>
<l>            yōṅkirum puṉṉai variniḻa liruntu</l>
<l>            tēṅkamaḻ tēṟal kiḷaiyoṭu māntip</l>
<l>            periya makiḻun tuṟaivaṉeñ</l>
<l>            ciṟiya neñcat takalvaṟi yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>          Alas, oh friend, how did pallor</l>
<l>          come to [our] good forehead?</l>
<l>          The man from the ghat, where the fishermen</l>
<l rend="indent2">            with firm boats [and] fast-moving hooks to be thrown,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            tied to the end of a rope with enduring strands,</l>
<l rend="indent">            take bright lights [and] go to hunt at midnight,</l>
<l rend="indent">            bring fish from the ocean at dawn,</l>
<l rend="indent">            heap [them] in the seashore [and then] enjoy themselves greatly,</l>
<l rend="indent">            drinking with [their] relatives of the toddy fragrant of honey,</l>
<l rend="indent">            sitting in the dappled shade of the high dark Puṉṉai tree,</l>
<l>          he does not know of departing from our heart [even] a little<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ciriya</term>: here T.V.G. wants to read an adjective, but since <term xml:lang="ta">neñcam</term> can in no way be supposed to be a neuter pl., he has to take it as an adjective of the modern type (for which we would want parallels). An adverb has admittedly the problem that it would split <term xml:lang="ta">em</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">neñcam</term>.</note>.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
